I move to amend Senate Bill No. 1623 as follows:
1. On Page 4, Line 4, by deleting after the word “Board” and before the word “be”, the word
“shall”, and inserting the word “may”;
2. On Page 17, Line 7, by deleting after the word “Board” and before the word “not”, the word
“shall”, and inserting the word “may”;
3. On Page 17, Line 10, by deleting after the word “Board” and before the word “permit”, the word
“shall”, and inserting the word “may”;
4. On Page 17, Line 10, by deleting after the word “union” and before the word “by”, the word
“charted”, and inserting the word “chartered”;
5. On Page 17, Line 11, by deleting after the word “of” and before the word “as”, the word
“associations”, and inserting the word “association”; and
6. On Page 17, Line 14, by inserting after the second comma and before the word “underserved”,
the words “persons with income at or below one hundred fifty percent (150%) of the United States
Department of Health and Human Services Poverty Guidelines residing in”.
